description.narrative: The project's development objective is to provide better access and transport services to rural and urban communities especially by improving key rural infrastructure in Mali and urban transport infrastructure in Bamako. Its specific objectives are to: (i) improve rural access in order to promote growth-supporting rural and agro-industrial business activities in cotton-growing areas; (ii) facilitate minibus traffic by creating a bus-only lane on Bamako's Boulevard du Peuple (People's Boulevard) and reconstructing a dedicated circular road in downtown Bamako, and (iii) strengthen the capacity of ministries and entities involved in the sector.
